🧠 VECTOR DATABASE — COMPLETE WORKFLOW (INPUT → OUTPUT)
🔥 0. Big Picture (don’t skip this)

System has 3 core parts:

Embedding Model → converts text to vector
Vector DB → stores & searches vectors
LLM (optional) → generates final answer

  ⚙️ 1. DATA INGESTION (Storing your data)
Step 1: Raw Data Input
You start with:
PDFs / Docs / Text / Website / Database
Example:   "Our refund policy lasts 7 days..."


Step 2: Chunking (VERY IMPORTANT)
👉 You don’t store full documents.
You split into smaller pieces:
Chunk 1: "Our refund policy lasts 7 days"
Chunk 2: "No refund after 7 days."
Why?
Embeddings work better on small chunks
Improves search accuracy
👉 If you skip this → garbage results


Step 3: Convert Text → Embeddings
Each chunk goes into the embedding model
Chunk → Embedding Model → Vector
Example:
"Our refund policy lasts 7 days."
→ [0.12, -0.88, 0.45, ...]


  
